{"article_id":"4EER3bcXMMMUAihC","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Ryan said little of the talks beyond ,","depth":3},{"id":1,"text":"'We ' re making progress .","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"We ' re talking . '","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"Ryan , Murray closer to budget deal","depth":2},{"id":4,"text":"House and Senate negotiators are pushing to finalize a small-scale deal","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"to set spending levels","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"and replace sequester cuts for the next two years ,","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"a potential respite in the bitter budget wars","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"consuming Congress .","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"The two congressional budget leaders","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"- Rep. Paul Ryan","depth":11},{"id":11,"text":"( R-Wis. )","depth":11},{"id":12,"text":"and Sen. Patty Murray","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"( D-Wash. ) -","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"are considering a plan","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"that would give relief to some of the domestic and defense programs most burdened by the sequester through 2015","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"by replacing those cuts with budgetary savings in other areas ,","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"according to sources familiar with the negotiations .","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"New revenue through fee increases","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"- not tax hikes -","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"is likely .","depth":6},{"id":21,"text":"The emerging plan also would attempt to find a middle ground between overall federal spending levels","depth":5},{"id":22,"text":"sought by Ryan and Murray in their respective budget plans .","depth":5},{"id":23,"text":"Under one proposal still under consideration , overall discretionary spending levels would be set in the $ 1 trillion range for 2014 ,","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"sources say .","depth":7},{"id":25,"text":"That ' s an uptick from the $ 967 billion spending level under the Budget Control Act but lower than the $ 1.058 trillion level","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"initially sought by Senate Democrats .","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"If the two sides agree to that approach ,","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"the increase in spending would be split about evenly between defense and nondefense spending ,","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"sources said .","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"Roughly $ 80 billion of the sequester cuts would instead be shifted to other programs in the federal budget ,","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"but overall deficit reduction would remain unchanged .","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"On Monday evening , Ryan said little of the talks beyond :","depth":4},{"id":33,"text":"\" We ' re making progress .","depth":5},{"id":34,"text":"We ' re talking . \"","depth":5},{"id":35,"text":"The target","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"to reach a deal","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"is Dec. 13","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"and a pact would reduce the chances of a government shutdown in 2014","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"- a midterm election year","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"in which House Republicans are trying to keep the majority .","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"The details are still being hammered out","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"-","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"and there remains a distinct possibility","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"that the effort will flounder ,","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"as so many budget deals have .","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"Still , the fact","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"that Ryan and Murray are this close to inking a deal","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"is significant .","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"It was just two months ago that Democrats and Republicans were so firmly entrenched on fiscal policy","depth":6},{"id":50,"text":"that Washington tumbled into the first government shutdown in 17 years .","depth":6},{"id":51,"text":"The Ryan-Murray discussions are playing out","depth":6},{"id":52,"text":"as another potential shutdown looms next month .","depth":6},{"id":53,"text":"Recognizing","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"that the talks could always collapse ,","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"Speaker John Boehner","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"( R-Ohio )","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"is prepared to pass a bill next week","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"that would fund the government past Jan. 15 at $ 967 billion","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"if no deal is reached between Murray and Ryan .","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"While Senate Democrats are adamantly opposed to setting spending at that low level ,","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"sources said Tuesday","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"that Senate Majority Leader Harry Reid","depth":13},{"id":63,"text":"( D-Nev. )","depth":13},{"id":64,"text":"would be prepared to accept a fallback , stop-gap measure at $ 967 billion","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"to avoid another shutdown .","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"But","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"if Murray and Ryan can agree on a budget framework","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"it would restore order to the dysfunctional congressional budget process","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"since the two sides will have agreed to overall spending levels , possibly for the next two fiscal years .","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"For that reason , House GOP leaders","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"- burned by the previous shutdown fight -","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"are eager to reach a deal now","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"and take the prospects of another politically disastrous episode off the table in an election year .","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"House GOP insiders say","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"a deal could be introduced as soon as late this week , with floor action next week .","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"Boehner has been eager to adjourn for the year by Dec. 13 .","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"Senior GOP sources on Monday said","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"the House would stick around past Dec. 13","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"if it were clear a deal would come together .","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"Sources said","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"the two sides have been centering on a plan","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"that would set 2014 spending levels around $ 990 billion ,","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"but on Monday aides said","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"that level was not the exact target","depth":12},{"id":85,"text":"and that the level may exceed $ 1 trillion for the next two fiscal years .","depth":12}],"relations":[{"parent":171,"left":89,"right":170,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":89,"left":88,"right":3,"relation":"restatement","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":88,"left":0,"right":87,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":87,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"restatement","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":170,"left":116,"right":169,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":116,"left":105,"right":115,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":105,"left":93,"right":104,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":93,"left":91,"right":92,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":91,"left":4,"right":90,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":90,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":92,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":104,"left":101,"right":103,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":101,"left":100,"right":17,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":100,"left":98,"right":99,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":98,"left":97,"right":14,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":97,"left":95,"right":96,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":95,"left":9,"right":94,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":94,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":96,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":99,"left":15,"right":16,"relation":"mode","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":103,"left":102,"right":20,"relation":"same-